The eByte whitepaper and executive summary offer valuable insights into the project.  Here is a short abstract out of the Whitepaper:  ____________________     eSports is a big business–ßand getting bigger. What started as a hobby or casual pastime for many people–ß  competing against other players in online video games–ßhas quickly evolved into a global business that generates  hundreds of millions of dollars annually. Yet, despite the rapid growth in eSports revenue, only a few recognized  professional players are well-compensated. Most players receive little or nothing in return for their skill and commitment.  At the same time, eSports teams often lack the resources to equip players with the latest technology.  And without guaranteed compensation, talented players frequently switch teams in search of better opportunities,  making it difficult for teams to manage their rosters and attract investors and sponsors. Similarly, leagues and event  and tournament organizers have no financial resources ‚Ä†to promote their activities or support the growth of their projects.  Therefore, people such as moderators, administrators, and service providers receive no compensation for their work.     The eByte project is developing a consortium blockchain, in cooperation with Draglet,  to establish the first international monetary system specifically designed for the eSports community...         PROJECT WHITEPAPER   EXECUTIVE SUMMARY               Despite the amazing market potential and growth, eSports currently lacks in possibilities that are fundamental for its future development.  Our vision with eByte is to contribute to the maturation of eSports by solving the following challenges:                                    Through simple mining, users contribute to the security of the network and the decentralized  creation of new eBytes, which enables them to generate revenue for their leagues, their teams or  themselves. Author: eByteBlockchain
Title: [ANN] eByte - Blockchain | eSports Ecosystem - Last Few Days for 30% BONUS ‚öΩÔ∏èüèÄ
Body: Thanks for that question LoveCryptoAll My name is Tim and im the Co-Founder of the project. Let me explain the eByte ecosystem to you.  Our project is creating an Blockchain in cooperation with Draglet aligned on the needs of the eSports community. With the Blockchain and the upcoming eByte cryptocoin we will establish a widely usable compensation system for the eSports community.  A small example with one of our target audiences (Players):  Players will finally receive compensation for their time spent. Many hours of the week flow into planning, training and implementation. A lot of investment flows into eSports. They are giving their full commitment for this hobby. But only the top players and with that the tip of the eSport-iceberg receive any kind of reward for it. With the eByte ecosystem players can benefit from their enthusiasm and also enhance their gaming equipment through mining, mini-cash games, betting portals and eByte trading. So even when the most players arent compensated for their time right now, with the eByte there will be a simple and secure way of generating income via several ways (described in the whitepaper).  Another example is for the target audience "eSports leagues":  Currently there is a high administrative and financial effort when operating a league. The leagues usually have a lot of work to do and often also insufficient sources of revenue. Through the eByte now the very simple possibility to increase the attractiveness of a legaue exists by introducing price money. Start fees, license seats or shares of a leagues content can be established. By e.g. mining or donating additional sources of revenue for the free and sustainable growth of the leagues are created. Moreover the eByte Blockchain and Smart Contracts ensure safe transactions and trust, as well as transparent metrics that allow leagues to become more interesting to sponsors.   So both of those target groups benefit from the ecosystem AND they are obviously connected with each other. Besides them there are many other target audiences that will join our ecosystem like service providers (graphic designers), online-shops (gamers will be able to buy hardware etc. with eBytes) or people donating streamers (using eByte for it).  With all those audiences involved the whole eByte ecosystem will be possible, since we already have many partners out of the audiences I talked about, that will participate in the project (see our website). Additionally there will be dynamic smart contracts for automated compensation & player contracts as well as several in-house platforms that will give the eByte more possibilities of use -> Whitepaper  I hope this answer clarifies the idea of the eByte system. If you have any more questions join our Discord (https://discordapp.com/invite/mq8sY2U)    Thanks, Tim
